choices.text: not getting lice and not being exposed to sun everyday at school. I'm too dark you see, and I need a pack of hats to cover my face and body. Those two problems became a challenge for me as I grew into that teenager who wanted to express himself and wanted to try those "cool" haircuts. And yes, I've tried. And yes, I have been rebuked as a kid or two and a scolding from my mother. See the result there? Are you telling me to get rid of them? Mom is right, she is always right! Mom was always right! I was caught in a turmoil. For a moment I thought it was because of how people see me. It couldn't the reason why, right? And traveling to developing countries helped me get through my bouts with lice, the darker the skin in the population, they refrained from dealing with my hair, a thing that I hated most.Well, that was not the rare condition I have experienced. I have had other problems as well, and it concerns diet. In the islands it wasn't a problem for me really, and my mom's secret for keeping control of my weight was by breastfeeding me up to 5 years of age. Talk about having that "thick frame" and people would go WTF that was! I was told I talked when I was 6 months old and when I was 7 years old, I completely stopped talking, until I read a story
